            <div class="col-md-4 padding2 center">
                <p>An interactive GIS map of multiple environmental cleanup layers, able to be filtered by layers</p>
                <hr>
                <ul class="left">
                    <li><b>Brownfield:</b> a property whose expansion, redevelopment, or use is complicated due to
                        actual or potential hazardous/petroleum contamination that may pose a risk to human health and the
                        environment</li>
                    <br>
                    <li><b>Dry Cleaners & Laundries:</b> these businesses release chemicals may contaminate water or soil</li>
                    <br>
                    <li><b>EPA Cleanups:</b> cleanups managed by the Environmental Protection Agency</li> 
                    <br>
                    <li><b>Hazardous Waste Corrective Action:</b> the current investigation and cleanup of hazardous waste</li>
                    <br>
                    <li><b>Leaking Underground Storage Tanks:</b> Leaking Underground Storage Tanksand their associated
                        piping can release chemical vapors into buildings or contaminate soil, surface water, and groundwater</li>
                    <br>
                    <li><b>Restricted Sites:</b> sites where Institutional Controls are required</li>
                    <br>
                    <li><b>Site Investigation:</b> under assessment for inclusion on the National Priorities List of the federal Superfund program</li>
                    <br>
                    <li><b>State Cleanup:</b> sites are contaminated with hazardous substances, but are not included on
                        the National Priorities List of the federal Superfund program</li>
                    <br>
                    <li><b>Superfund:</b> created by the partnership between Office of Land Qualityâ€™s Superfund and the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency to clean up sites contaminated with hazardous waste that may require complex investigations, significant cleanup actions, and long-term attention</li>
                    <br>
                    <li><b>Voluntary Remediation Program:</b> encourages environmental cleanups; facilitates the redevelopment, sale, and reuse of commercial and industrial properties; and reduces the risks that contaminants pose to human health and the environment</li>
                </ul>
